<h2>Implementation Details</h2>
<p>The sunâ€™s event listener will call the service when the sun rises or sets with
an offset.</p>
<p>The sun event need to have the type â€˜sunâ€™, which service to call,
which event (sunset or sunrise) and the offset.</p>
<pre><code class="language-json">{
    &quot;type&quot;: &quot;sun&quot;,
    &quot;service&quot;: &quot;switch.turn_on&quot;,
    &quot;event&quot;: &quot;sunset&quot;,
    &quot;offset&quot;: &quot;-01:00:00&quot;
}
</code></pre>
<h3>Maintains entity <code>sun.sun</code></h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Possible state</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>above_horizon</code></td>
<td>When the sun is above the horizon.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>below_horizon</code></td>
<td>When the sun is below the horizon.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>State Attributes</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><code>next_rising</code></td>
<td>Date and time of the next sun rising (in UTC).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>next_setting</code></td>
<td>Date and time of the next sun setting (in UTC).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>next_dawn</code></td>
<td>Date and time of the next dawn (in UTC).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>next_dusk</code></td>
<td>Date and time of the next dusk (in UTC).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>next_noon</code></td>
<td>Date and time of the next solar noon (in UTC).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>next_midnight</code></td>
<td>Date and time of the next solar midnight (in UTC).</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>elevation</code></td>
<td>Solar elevation. This is the angle between the sun and the horizon. Negative values mean the sun is below the horizon.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>azimuth</code></td>
<td>Solar azimuth. The angle is shown clockwise from north.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><code>rising</code></td>
<td>True if the Sun is currently rising, after solar midnight and before solar noon.</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
